        skos:definition  "\nA straight line defined by it's end points.\n\nAttributes\n----------\nx1 : float\n    The X coordinate of the start of the line. [units pixels]\ny1 : float\n    The Y coordinate of the start of the line. [units pixels]\nx2 : float\n    The X coordinate of the end of the line. [units pixels]\ny2 : float\n    The Y coordinate of the end of the line. [units pixels]\nmarker_start : None | Marker\n    (The Line MarkerStart).\nmarker_end : None | Marker\n    (The Line MarkerEnd).";
        skos:inScheme    core: .

core:LightEmittingDiode
        rdf:type         owl:Class , linkml:ClassDefinition;
        rdfs:label       "LightEmittingDiode";
        rdfs:subClassOf  core:LightSource;
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type            owl:Restriction;
                           owl:minCardinality  0;
                           owl:onProperty      core:lot_number
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type           owl:Restriction;
                           owl:allValuesFrom  linkml:String;
                           owl:onProperty     core:model
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type            owl:Restriction;
                           owl:maxCardinality  1;
                           owl:onProperty      core:lot_number
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type            owl:Restriction;
                           owl:maxCardinality  1;
                           owl:onProperty      core:serial_number
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type           owl:Restriction;
                           owl:allValuesFrom  linkml:Integer;
                           owl:onProperty     core:power
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type            owl:Restriction;
                           owl:maxCardinality  1;
                           owl:onProperty      core:model
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type            owl:Restriction;
                           owl:maxCardinality  1;
                           owl:onProperty      core:power
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type           owl:Restriction;
                           owl:allValuesFrom  linkml:String;
                           owl:onProperty     core:serial_number
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type            owl:Restriction;
                           owl:maxCardinality  1;
                           owl:onProperty      core:manufacturer
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type            owl:Restriction;
                           owl:minCardinality  0;
                           owl:onProperty      core:model
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type            owl:Restriction;
                           owl:minCardinality  0;
                           owl:onProperty      core:serial_number
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type           owl:Restriction;
                           owl:allValuesFrom  linkml:String;
                           owl:onProperty     core:manufacturer
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type            owl:Restriction;
                           owl:minCardinality  0;
                           owl:onProperty      core:power
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type           owl:Restriction;
                           owl:allValuesFrom  linkml:String;
                           owl:onProperty     core:lot_number
                         ];
        rdfs:subClassOf  [ rdf:type            owl:Restriction;
                           owl:minCardinality  0;
                           owl:onProperty      core:manufacturer
                         ];
        skos:definition  "\nThe LightEmittingDiode element is used to describe various kinds of LED\nlamps. As the LightEmittingDiode is inside a LightSource it already has\navailable the values from ManufacturerSpec (Manufacturer, Model, SerialNumber,\nLotNumber) And the values from LightSource which includes Power in milliwatts\nWe have looked at extending this element but have had a problem producing a\ngeneric solution.\n\nPossible attributes talked about adding include:\nPower in lumens - but this is complicated by multi-channel\ndevices like CoolLED where each channel's power is different\nWavelength Range - not a simple value so would require\nmultiple attributes or a child element\nAngle of Projection - this would be further affected by the\noptics used for filtering the naked LED or that combine\npower from multiple devices\nThese values are further affected if you over-drive the LED\nresulting in a more complex system\nAnother issue is that LED's may not be used directly for\nillumination but as drivers for secondary emissions from doped\nfiber optics. This would require the fiber optics to be modeled.\nThanks to Paul Goodwin of Applied Precision of information about\nthis topic.";
        skos:inScheme    core: .

core:Reference  rdf:type  linkml:ClassDefinition , owl:Class;
        rdfs:label       "Reference";
        skos:definition  "\nReference is an empty complex type that is contained and extended by all the\n*Ref elements and also the Settings Complex Type Each *Ref element defines an\nattribute named ID of simple type *ID and no other information Each simple type\n*ID is restricted to the base type LSID with an appropriate pattern.";
        skos:inScheme    core: .

core:Leader  rdf:type    linkml:ClassDefinition , owl:Class;
        rdfs:label       "Leader";
        rdfs:subClassOf  core:Reference;
        skos:definition  "\nContact information for a ExperimenterGroup leader specified using a reference\nto an Experimenter element defined elsewhere in the document.";
        skos:inScheme    core: .

